<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1424047" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/courts.png?resize=600%2C400&#038;ssl=1" alt="Ondo court terminates contempt suit against Speaker, three others" width="600" height="400" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/courts.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/courts.png?resize=300%2C200&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/courts.png?resize=58%2C39&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/courts.png?resize=260%2C173&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/courts.png?resize=195%2C130&amp;ssl=1 195w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/courts.png?resize=115%2C77&amp;ssl=1 115w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> A 23-year-old sales representative, Sunday Olanrewaju, on Thursday appeared before a Tinubu Chief Magistrates’ Court, Lagos, for allegedly stealing a wig worth N200,000 from his employer’s shop. Olanrewaju, whose address was not provided, is facing a charge of stealing to which he pleaded not guilty. The prosecutor, Insp. Ajaga Agboko, told the court that the defendant committed the offence on Dec. 10, 2020, at 2.00 p.m. at BO Hair Salon, Lekki Phase 1, Lagos. Agboko said that the defendant stole a Peruvian hair wig, belonging to the complainant, Mrs Oluomachi Onzunike. He said the offence contravened Section 287 (7) of the Criminal Law of Lagos, 2015. Recall that the section stipulates seven years imprisonment for stealing from one’s employer. The Magistrate, Mrs T.A. Idowu, granted the defendant N50,000 bail with one surety in like sum. Idowu adjourned the case until Jan. 19 for mention. A 34-year-old bus conductor, Dolapo Pine, who allegedly stole a passenger’s Automated Teller Machine (ATM) card and withdrew N82,000 with it, on Monday appeared before a Tinubu Magistrates’ Court in Lagos State. February 24, 2020 In "News" Two sales representatives, who allegedly stole hair extensions worth N3.3 million belonging to their employer, were on Wednesday brought before a Tinubu Chief Magistrates’ Court in Lagos. October 24, 2018 In "News" 57-year-old landlord, Jamiu Animashaun, was on Monday docked at a Tinubu Magistrates’ Court in Lagos for allegedly defrauding his female tenant of N1.5 million on the pretext of selling her a vehicle. October 14, 2019 In "News"